      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RAKERO WARRIOR NZ (10) continues a run of second row draws but continues to race well from there with three wins and a second from his last five starts. Worked to the front before going on to score by 6.7m last week, his third win from five tries here. Proven at this distance so could strike again. CHARLIES TACTICS (2) added to his consistent form when he raced parked but stuck on for a 1.4m second at Bendigo last time. Draws closer to the pegs and has only once missed the top-three in eight starts so he is reliable. OX KNOX (3) was a beaten favourite last start but had to race three wide without cover so there was merit in his effort to box on for fourth. SHES SKY HIGH (7) came from a similar barrier to this for a resuming fourth at Geelong. Races well second up so should be improved and goes well at this shorter distance. AETOS DYNAMIS (5) did a good job to come from the back row for a 3.6m third at Bendigo last time out.",
